.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH g-stats 1  "g-stats " 
.SH NAME
g\-stats \- Display a rich usage\-statistics report
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBg\-stats\fR [\fB\-\-days\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-git\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Display a rich usage\-statistics report
.PP
Aggregates data from the internal SQLite database (command runs, commits recorded via `g commit`) and the current repository\*(Aqs git history to produce a terminal report that includes:
.PP
• Overview totals and streak information • GitHub\-style commit heatmap for the last 52 weeks • Lines\-added / lines\-removed sparkline (current branch) • Top commands by frequency • Conventional\-commit type distribution • Repository activity ranking • Activity\-by\-hour chart
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-days\fR \fI<DAYS>\fR [default: 365]
Number of days to look back for time\-based stats
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-git\fR
Skip sections that require a git repository (heatmap, lines chart)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH EXTRA
Examples:

  g stats                    full report, last 365 days
  g stats \-\-days 90           last 90 days
  g stats \-\-no\-git            skip sections that require git
